summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of North Forty-sixth Avenue from Fremont Avenue to Palatine Avenue et al in the City of Seattle, by constructing concrete walks under Ordinance No. 20052, creating Local Improvement District No. 1934 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
